<br>
As I was running from the wonderful train of Drybones, Carrion Ghouls, Festering Hags, and the many Death beetles that our wonderful Ealwen trained the other night in unrest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , it occured to me that this would be a good place for a guild raid.  Unrest is good for almost anyone above the level 11.  The younger members can hang by the fountain and take out the yard trash that spawns there.  The zone is quite close, so the occasion &quot;RUN!!!..TRAIN&quot; should give them enough warning to head for the zone.  The higher levels 15-20 can head towards the back wall and take on the numerous ghouls and skellies that can be pulled from within the estate while the higher levels can go deeper in and explore the Pit and Magi room.<br>
<br>
In my experience, Unrest has been very good experience, and decent loot for lower levels, bronze weapons, ringmail and jewels droppings are common.  If you can keep away from the train, it migght be pretty fun<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
