<br>
Within the Butcherblock Mountains, there is a 3 way intersection of paths in roughly the middle of the zone.  This is called the crossroads, or xroads by those who frequent the zone.  If you were heading to Greater Faydark from Kaladim (or the docks), you would take a left on the path.  You, however, will want to take a right at this crossing.  This will lead you to Dagnor's cauldron, home to the entrances of 2 of Norrath's least popular dungeons.  From the entrance of Dagnor's cauldron, go down the twisting path until you reach the actual cauldron.  Once the path expands into the actual zone, there are two semi-safe ways of reaching Unrest.  The first, is to hug the right wall until you see the big gaping hole in the side of the stone, which is the entrance to Unrest.  This route can be potentally dangerous because of the extremely steep drops.  If you take your time, It might work out for you, sow is out of the question <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The second way is to go straight forward once the zone expands out, until you hit the water.  Then proceed to hug the shore going right.  Take your time when doing this, there are a huge amount of aqua goblins of levels 15-24 wandering the entire zone.  However, if you see a goblin named Bilge, stop immediately and give Dolumar or I a tell. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (18 wis items tend to get me excited <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  Continue along the shore until you see a large green patch of moss (or I think it's moss... never could tell), soon after that, the shore should be at a near vertical angle.  At that point, you want to leave the shore and head straight south (which will be to your right) and you should see the large opening in the rock, which is Unrest.  I'll escort a couple people there myself if this raid takes place.  <br>
<br>
On getting back...<br>
The best way back is simply to hug the wall on the left after you exit unrest.  That will bring you back to the path which will lead you to Butcherblock.  Or you can follow the shore back, this time taking a left once you hit the water.  (Be careful when heading to the shore though, been hit for 90 odd falling damage in that spot a couple times, seeing that it's nearly vertical)  After heading about 200 feet, you can climb up off the shore, and stay on the ridge until you hit the npc camp.. Once you hit the npc camp, simply go straight ahead towards the large brown splotch of dead grass... moss... or somesuch.  Once upon that hill you'll be able to see the entrance of the path to Butcherblock.  Again, I'll be giving escorts, I realize that this is probably overly confusing.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions about Unrest, or the directions, be sure to give me a tell or email me at schuurjg.muohio.edu<br>
Thanks and good luck!<br>
Ealwen Imladris, Cleric of the 35th Season<br>
